        best_for: ['SaaS Founders and "Build in Public" entrepreneurs on Twitter', 'B2B Sales Executives executing "Social Selling" on LinkedIn', 'Social Media Ghostwriters handling intense comment engagement', 'Anyone who knows they need to comment more to grow their audience but suffers from "blank screen" anxiety'],
        pros: ['It fundamentally solves the massive time-drain of active social networking; allowing a user to engage intelligently with 100 people in 20 minutes instead of 3 hours', 'The ability to set custom prompts (e.g., "Always relate the reply back to the concept of email marketing") is a brilliant, subtle way to drive top-of-funnel traffic to a specific niche without looking like a spammer', 'By actually reading the context of the massive thread before replying, it avoids the terrifying embarrassment of posting a generic "Nice!" on a post about a serious tragedy', 'It acts as excellent conversational training wheels for introverted founders who desperately want to network digitally but feel profound anxiety about what to say to massive influencers'],
